    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/torn-veggie-nduja-lasagne-and-balsamic-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> plant based</strong> <strong>'Nduja </strong>and the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/torn-veggie-nduja-lasagne-and-balsamic-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[275ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and<strong> half </strong>your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Bring to the boil, then cook for 5-6 min or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/torn-veggie-nduja-lasagne-and-balsamic-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Break your <strong>lasagne sheets </strong>into medium-sized pieces and add them to the boiling water, stirring to separate the pasta pieces \u2013 this is your <strong>torn lasagne</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min, stirring from time to time to prevent the pasta from sticking, then drain the <strong>cooked lasagne</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/torn-veggie-nduja-lasagne-and-balsamic-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>spinach</strong> and cook for 1 min or until wilted</p><p>Once wilted, add the <strong>cooked lasagne</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/torn-veggie-nduja-lasagne-and-balsamic-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dollop over your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, then sprinkle over your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> with a grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the lid on and cook for a final 2 min or until the cheese has melted \u2013 this is your <strong>torn</strong> <strong>veggie 'Nduja lasagne</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/torn-veggie-nduja-lasagne-and-balsamic-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/torn-veggie-nduja-lasagne-and-balsamic-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>torn</strong> <strong>veggie 'Nduja lasagne </strong>and sprinkle over the <strong>chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salad </strong>to the side with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and the<strong> remaining balsamic vinegar</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
